The Mage Guild defines several unique emotes for the enjoyment of its
members.  Some of these allow you to do standard emotions in a different
way than other players, while others are mage guild originals that no
other players have.  You are always free to post your ideas for new
emotes on the guild bulletin board and they might get put into the game.
 
Bow      You bow with a flourish.  Can be done at a person and afar.
Chin     You stroke your chin thoughtfully.
Curtsey  You curtsey with a flourish.  Same as bow.
Eureka!  You get an idea!
Fumble   You botch a spell and are enveloped in an explosion.  No SP
         used and no damage is done.  Fumble is purely for fun.  Other
         people will see you coughing and brushing off your robes.
         Fumble is a color emote.
Glow     You glow with magical energy.  Glow is a color emote.
Grin     You grin disarmingly.  Can be done at a person and afar.
Gronk    Just a fun emote.  Meaningless, but fun nonetheless.
Know     You are very knowledgeable.  If 'know <subject>' is typed then
         you will be very knowledgeable about <subject>.
Motion   Motion to someone that they will shortly be receiving some goodies
         from you.  This is best used with gate or the Darkwind UPS service.
Mthink   Requires input. You think about . o O ( what you input )
         Think is a color emote.
Nimbus   You wave your hands, and then you're surrounded by a glowing nimbus
         of energy.  Nimbus is a color emote.
Nod      You nod understandingly.  Can be done at a person and afar.
Spark    Give someone a really big jolt in the butt!
Tag      Sneak up behind someone and tag them IT!
Tuna     Slap someone in the face with a big, slimy, wet tuna.
Whatever Let someone (or the room you're in) know that you don't believe them.
